      • doWithExclusiveLock

        public <R> R doWithExclusiveLock(Function<TableStore<T>,? extends R> code)
        Description copied from interface: TableStore
        Acquires file-system level lock on the underlying file, to prevent concurrent access from multiple processes. It is recommended to use this when acquiring your values for the first time, otherwise it is possible to get unpredictable results in case of multiple processes/threads trying to acquire values for the same key. In addition, it allows to batch multiple TableStore.acquireValueFor(CharSequence) calls, to atomically acquire multiple values.
        Specified by:
        doWithExclusiveLock in interface TableStore<T extends Metadata>
        Type Parameters:
        R - result type
        Parameters:
        code - code block to execute using locked table store
        Returns:
